==English==

===Adjective===
'''horny'''  ({{compar}}: '''[[hornier]]''', {{superl}}: '''[[horniest]]''')

# [[Hard]] or [[bony]], like an animal’s [[horn]].
# (''coarse slang'') Sexually aroused.
#:Her thick, gurgling voice saying...: "Get it in all the way…please, please do... I’m ''horny''."--Henry Miller ''Sexus,'' (1949) v. 104
#:When...he used to make a habit of watching the hockey games...he always felt ''horny''.--Mordecai Richler ''Cocksure'' (1968) xi. 63
#:Ain’t that the ''horny'' bitch that was grindin with the blind dude.--''Black World,'' Oct. 1971, 65/1
#:That chick makes me feel ''horny''.
# (''coarse slang'') Sexually arousing.
#:That chick is so ''horny''!

====Synonyms====
*(''hard or bony''): [[callous]], [[coarse]], [[coarsen]]ed, [[harden]]ed, [[rough]]
*(''sexually aroused''): [[randy]]
*(''sexually arousing''): [[hot]], [[sexy]]

